subSubSection.paragraph:
Native to the Palaearctic region. Widespread in Europe, also recorded from Iran and Turkey (
Kazantsev and Brancucci 2007
). Adventive in the Nearctic region (British Columbia, Alberta, Saskatchewan, Manitoba, Ontario, Quebec, New Brunswick, Nova Scotia, Prince Edward Island, and Newfoundland, Canada).

