In Europe, this eurytopic species is usually found in dry, warm habitats such as exposed forest edges, dry meadows etc. (
Koch 1989b
). The larvae probably live in dead wood as predators (
Koch 1989b
). The Canadian specimens were collected in a variety of habitats, mainly forests, and mainly in Malaise traps.
